<Layout
	lang="en"
	title="Services & Conditions — Gandía, summer 2026"
	description="Local consultancy for your summer 2026 holiday on Spain's Mediterranean coast — hotel and itinerary recommendations, 24/7 WhatsApp support, translation help, on-the-ground guidance. You book and pay; we plan and support."
	otherLangHref="/es/servicios/"
	otherLangLabel="Español"
>
	<p class="eyebrow">Services &amp; Conditions</p>
	<h1>What we <span class="accent">do</span></h1>
	<p class="tagline">
		Local consultancy for your summer on the Valencian coast — recommendations, translation and a hand on the ground. You make the bookings; we make the days work.
	</p>

	<p class="lead">
		People want to come to this corner of Spain, and most arrive with the same questions — where to stay, how to get there from the airport, what's worth seeing, where to swim, when to go to the aquapark, which mountain villages to drive up to. <strong>We live here.</strong> We tell you what we'd do, and then we're there on WhatsApp the whole time you're around.
	</p>

	<h2>What we help with</h2>

	<h3>Planning your stay</h3>
	<p>
		Tell us your dates, who's coming, your budget and the shape of the days you'd like — slow beach, mountain villages, family pace, the eclipse on 12 August, food trips, a quiet base in the sierras. We come back with hotel recommendations that fit, transfer options, a day-by-day shape for the trip and the bookings worth doing ahead of time.
	</p>

	<h3>Once you arrive</h3>
	<p>
		We're on WhatsApp <strong>24/7</strong> while you're in the area. The day's best restaurant, the right beach for the wind that morning, a last-minute reservation, where to park, the weather to expect — quick answers, in English or Spanish.
	</p>

	<h3>What we can point you to</h3>
	<p>The kind of things we recommend, arrange or help with:</p>
	<ul class="services-grid">
		<li>Hotels and apartments by area and budget</li>
		<li>Airport pick-up and drop-off (Valencia, Alicante)</li>
		<li>Car rental — who to use, what size, where to pick up</li>
		<li>Bike and e-bike rental, road and mountain routes</li>
		<li>Restaurant recommendations &amp; reservations</li>
		<li>Beaches, calas and snorkelling spots up and down the coast</li>
		<li>Aquaparks — which one, which day, when to avoid the crush</li>
		<li>Hiking routes, summit walks, river pools</li>
		<li>Lakes, waterfalls and gorges worth the drive</li>
		<li>Castles, old towns and cultural day trips (Guadalest, Xàtiva, Valencia)</li>
		<li>The 12 August eclipse — where to watch, where to drive</li>
		<li>The Perseids (11–13 August) — dark spots ten minutes inland</li>
		<li>Concerts, festivals and local events while you're here</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Guided support</h3>
	<p>
		For some of the above we can come with you as a guide — a half-day in the old town, a drive up to Guadalest, an eclipse evening on the coast. Just ask.
	</p>

	<h3>Translation &amp; emergencies</h3>
	<p>
		Many locals don't speak English. We help you communicate — with the hotel, the doctor, the rental agency, a shopkeeper. <strong>If something goes wrong</strong> — a medical or dental situation, a problem with the car, a lost document — we'll come along to translate and help you sort it out. You won't be on your own in a country whose language you may not speak.
	</p>

	<h2>How it works</h2>
	<ol class="how-list">
		<li><strong>You write to us</strong> with your dates, who's coming, your budget and what you'd like out of the trip.</li>
		<li><strong>We come back with a plan</strong> — recommendations, options, prices we've seen, a shape for the days.</li>
		<li><strong>You decide, book and pay yourselves</strong> — hotels, flights, car rental, restaurants. We give you the where and the how; the reservations are yours.</li>
		<li><strong>You arrive</strong> — we meet you or we're on WhatsApp from the moment you land, and we stay reachable until you leave.</li>
	</ol>

	<h2>What we are — and aren't</h2>
	<p>
		We are a <strong>local consultancy</strong>, not a travel agency. Everything we suggest is a <strong>recommendation</strong>, based on what we know and on your preferences. The decisions, the bookings, the payments and the contracts are <strong>entirely yours</strong> — you check, you approve, you pay, and you handle the reservations directly with hotels, rental companies, restaurants and tour operators. We act on the ground and in the local context, but the legal and financial responsibility for your trip stays with you.
	</p>
	<p>
		If you'd prefer that one company handles everything end-to-end, a travel agency is the right choice. If you want someone local on the line who knows the coast and answers in English at 11pm — that's us.
	</p>

	<p class="data-promise">
		<strong>We will never ask for your passport, ID number, card details, bank information or any other sensitive personal data.</strong> The only information we work with is the name and contact details (email or phone) that you choose to share with us — nothing more. Documents that bookings need stay between you and the hotel, rental company or service provider.
	</p>

	<h2>Support our work</h2>
	<p>
		We'd love to keep doing this year after year. If we've been useful to your trip and you'd like to chip in, you can support us on Ko-fi — it helps us keep the answers fast and the recommendations honest.
	</p>
	<p class="cta-top">
		<a class="cta" href="https://ko-fi.com/luiza82" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Support us on Ko-fi →</a>
	</p>

	<hr />

	<p class="cta-top">
		<a class="cta" href="/contact/">Tell us about your trip →</a>
	</p>

